'''''Houstonia correllii''''', the '''Zapata County bluet,''' or '''Correll's bluet''', is a species of plants in the [[Rubiaceae]].<ref>[https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/13038911#page/447/mode/1up Terrell, Edward Everett. 1975.  Phytologia 31(6): 425. ''Houstonia correllii'']</ref><ref>Lewis, Walter Hepworth. 1972.  Brittonia 24(4): 395–397, f. 1–2. ''Hedyotis correllii''</ref> It is known only from [[Zapata County, Texas|Zapata]] County in southern [[Texas]]. It is a prostrate, mat-forming plant with white flowers.<ref>[http://bonap.net/MapGallery/County/Houstonia%20correllii.png Biota of North America Program]</ref>

